/r9k/ is an imageboard where there are no exact reposts.

1. If you attempt to post something unoriginal, it is not posted, and you are muted temporarily.
2. The time with which you are muted for doubles with each transgression.
3. Each mute time is 2^n in seconds where n is the number of times you have transgressed. So, your mute time doubles each time you fuck up.
4. Backlinks, eg >>1, are not viewed by the robot. So "lolwut" and ">>2 lolwut" are the same post, in the eyes of the robot.
5. Gibberish at the end of a post to force originality may result in mod intervention (no BLOX posts please).
6. Images are NOT included in the filter, only text.
7. Your mute count slowly decreases over time.
8. You cannot post a picture without text.
9. Unicode is blocked. Sorry, too many exploits (Cyrillic letters, etc).
10. Posts require a certain minimum amount of original content in order to be posted.
11. Post sane, real content, well thought out replies, and mutes are unlikely.
12. The original algorithm was designed by XKCD:
http://blag.xkcd.com/2008/01/14/robot9000-and-xkcd-signal-attacking-noise-in-chat/

>your type
>what fear response(s) do you typically resort to (afaik there are 4 (perhaps more, idk) - fight, flight, freeze, and fawn. I've also heard it said that giving up/shutting down can also be a fear response.)
I don't know if fear responses really line up with personality at all but mine kind of did so I thought this would be a good question potentially

ISFJ
I usually freeze or become very quiet both when I'm alerted to a possible threat and when I am aware that there is one, though I also inch toward "fight". I don't like having my back toward people or things that make me feel unsafe even to run away, so I don't run even though I'm a bit of a coward. Part of it also probably due to paralysis caused by indecision.
In some cases I very much have what feels like a primal urge to sucker punch a person because of how anxious and unsafe they are making me feel, but that's frowned upon unfortunately.

>what are you doing to better your self?
Trying to accept that I am different from others but that I still have some worth. It's harder some days than others. I find it hard to relate to others and yet I am most inspired by others. I suppose I am a pioneer in a weird way. I hope one day I can make something of myself and show others that may be like me that it's possible.

>>72118121
Small changes only give small benefits.
It's hard to give advice when it's unclear what the bottleneck is.
But some things you can do are:
Ensure your temps are good, modern parts (particularily laptops) will clock up to their thermal limits (although for older ryzen you have to manually enable PBO in bios).
Ensure XMP/DOCP is enabled in bios.
Enable resizable bar in bios and then windows if available.
If you're lacking in RAM run a windows debloater script.

If you're suffering from a weak GPU and are willing to make sacrifices you can dig through games' config files to lower settings and resolution scaling further. Some games might not allow lower than 1024x768 normally but can be forced lower in a config file e.g. 800x600 or 640x480 or a custom resolution like 960x540 which you can integer scale to 1080p if you like big chunky pixels.
